snippet: The New England Patriots released offensive lineman Kyler Kerbyson on Sunday to open a roster spot ahead of safety Nate Ebner returning to the team after competing for the U.S. Olympic rugby team at the Rio Olympics....
lead_paragraph: The New England Patriots released offensive lineman Kyler Kerbyson on Sunday to open a roster spot ahead of safety Nate Ebner returning to the team after competing for the U.S. Olympic rugby team at the Rio Olympics.

headline.main: Pats Prepare to Welcome Back U.S. Olympic Rugby Player Ebner
headline.print_headline: Pats Prepare to Welcome Back U.S. Olympic Rugby Player Ebner
